<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{5}{y}=-{16}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{8}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},{2}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+-{5}{y}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{16}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{16}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{\left(\frac{{-{16}-{\left(-{5}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}\right)}+{8}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{7}}{{2}}\cdot{\left(-{16}\right)}-\frac{{7}}{{2}}{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}+{8}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{56}-{\left({17.5}\right)}{y}+{8}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{17.5}{y}+{\left({8}\right)}{y}=-{5}--{56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{17.5}{y}+{\left({8}\right)}{y}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({17.5}+{\left({8}\right)}\right)}{y}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25.5}{y}={51}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{51}}{{25.5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={2}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+-{5}{\left({2}\right)}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left(-{10}\right)}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{16}-{\left(-{10}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{6}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{3},{2}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

